# Agent instructions (project workspace)

This directory is the **project workspace** for **___PROJECT___**. It was scaffolded by `just project-init` from your dotfiles; it is not necessarily a git repository root (git metadata lives under per-repo checkouts, described below).

## Layout (defaults under `$HOME/dev`)

- **`manifests/default.repos`**: list of `org/repo branch` lines used by `just new` to decide which canonical repositories participate in a task.
- **`tasks/<type>/<task-id>/`**: one folder per task. Each immediate child named after a repo basename is a **Jujutsu workspace** (when the canonical clone is jj-colocated) or a **`git worktree`** otherwise. Objects stay in the canonical clone; these directories are thin checkouts only.
- **`tasks/<type>/<task-id>/task.json`**: maps checkout folder names to `org/repo` for safe teardown (`just drop`).
- **`state/locks/`**, **`state/events/`**: reserved for coordination (empty until tooling uses them).

Canonical clones live under **`repos/<git-host>/<org>/<repo>`** (default host `github.com`), not under this project tree.

## Commands

Run **`just`** from **this directory** (the project root). Typical flow:

1. Edit `manifests/default.repos`.
2. **`DRY_RUN=1 just new <type> <task-id>`** to preview, then **`just new <type> <task-id>`** to create task checkouts.
3. **`just add <type> <task-id> <org/repo> …`** to attach more repos to an existing task.
4. **`just list`** / **`just list <type>`** to list tasks.
5. **`just drop …`** to remove tasks or selected repos; **`just drop`** with no further args removes the entire project (from the per-project `Justfile` only).

Override roots with **`DEV_ROOT`** and **`DEV_GIT_HOST`** when invoking `just`. Use **`DRY_RUN=1`** on `new` and `drop` for no-op previews.

## Version control

- Prefer **`jj`** for history and bookmarks when the canonical repo has a colocated **`.jj/`** directory; recipes fall back to **`git`** worktrees otherwise.
- Task branches (git) and bookmarks (jj) use **`<type>/___PROJECT___/<task-id>`**. Do not rewrite history in canonical clones without understanding shared use across tasks.

## Further reading

Upstream documentation for this workflow lives in the dotfiles repo: [docs/project-task-workspaces.md](https://github.com/aguil/dotfiles/blob/HEAD/docs/project-task-workspaces.md).
